00107 //********** Buffer Attributes **********
00108 #define DAQmx_Buf_Input_BufSize                                          0x186C // Specifies the number of samples the input buffer can hold for each channel in the task. Zero indicates to allocate no buffer. Use a buffer size of 0 to perform a hardware-timed operation without using a buffer. Setting this property overrides the automatic input buffer allocation that NI-DAQmx performs.
00109 #define DAQmx_Buf_Input_OnbrdBufSize                                     0x230A // Indicates in samples per channel the size of the onboard input buffer of the device.
00110 #define DAQmx_Buf_Output_BufSize                                         0x186D // Specifies the number of samples the output buffer can hold for each channel in the task. Zero indicates to allocate no buffer. Use a buffer size of 0 to perform a hardware-timed operation without using a buffer. Setting this property overrides the automatic output buffer allocation that NI-DAQmx performs.
00111 #define DAQmx_Buf_Output_OnbrdBufSize                                    0x230B // Specifies in samples per channel the size of the onboard output buffer of the device.

00115 #define DAQmx_SelfCal_LastTemp                                           0x1864 // Indicates in degrees Celsius the temperature of the device at the time of the last self calibration. Compare this temperature to the current onboard temperature to determine if you should perform another calibration.
00116 #define DAQmx_ExtCal_RecommendedInterval                                 0x1868 // Indicates in months the National Instruments recommended interval between each external calibration of the device.

Compare this temperature to the current onboard temperature to determine if you should perform another calibration.

00748 #define DAQmx_ArmStartTrig_Type                                          0x1414 // Specifies the type of trigger to use to arm the task for a Start Trigger. If you configure an Arm Start Trigger, the task does not respond to a Start Trigger until the device receives the Arm Start Trigger.
00749 #define DAQmx_DigEdge_ArmStartTrig_Src                                   0x1417 // Specifies the name of a terminal where there is a digital signal to use as the source of the Arm Start Trigger.
00750 #define DAQmx_DigEdge_ArmStartTrig_Edge                                  0x1415 // Specifies on which edge of a digital signal to arm the task for a Start Trigger.
00751 #define DAQmx_DigEdge_ArmStartTrig_DigFltr_Enable                        0x222D // Specifies whether to apply the pulse width filter to the signal.
00752 #define DAQmx_DigEdge_ArmStartTrig_DigFltr_MinPulseWidth                 0x222E // Specifies in seconds the minimum pulse width the filter recognizes.
00753 #define DAQmx_DigEdge_ArmStartTrig_DigFltr_TimebaseSrc                   0x222F // Specifies the input terminal of the signal to use as the timebase of the pulse width filter.
00754 #define DAQmx_DigEdge_ArmStartTrig_DigFltr_TimebaseRate                  0x2230 // Specifies in hertz the rate of the pulse width filter timebase. NI-DAQmx uses this value to compute settings for the filter.
00755 #define DAQmx_DigEdge_ArmStartTrig_DigSync_Enable                        0x2231 // Specifies whether to synchronize recognition of transitions in the signal to the internal timebase of the device.
00756 
00757 //********** Watchdog Attributes **********
00758 #define DAQmx_Watchdog_Timeout                                           0x21A9 // Specifies in seconds the amount of time until the watchdog timer expires. A value of -1 means the internal timer never expires. Set this input to -1 if you use an Expiration Trigger to expire the watchdog task.
00759 #define DAQmx_WatchdogExpirTrig_Type                                     0x21A3 // Specifies the type of trigger to use to expire a watchdog task.
00760 #define DAQmx_DigEdge_WatchdogExpirTrig_Src                              0x21A4 // Specifies the name of a terminal where a digital signal exists to use as the source of the Expiration Trigger.
00761 #define DAQmx_DigEdge_WatchdogExpirTrig_Edge                             0x21A5 // Specifies on which edge of a digital signal to expire the watchdog task.
00762 #define DAQmx_Watchdog_DO_ExpirState                                     0x21A7 // Specifies the state to which to set the digital physical channels when the watchdog task expires.  You cannot modify the expiration state of dedicated digital input physical channels.
00763 #define DAQmx_Watchdog_HasExpired                                        0x21A8 // Indicates if the watchdog timer expired. You can read this property only while the task is running.
00764 
00765 //********** Write Attributes **********
00766 #define DAQmx_Write_RelativeTo                                           0x190C // Specifies the point in the buffer at which to write data. If you also specify an offset with Offset, the write operation begins at that offset relative to this point you select with this property.
00767 #define DAQmx_Write_Offset                                               0x190D // Specifies in samples per channel an offset at which a write operation begins. This offset is relative to the location you specify with Relative To.
00768 #define DAQmx_Write_RegenMode                                            0x1453 // Specifies whether to allow NI-DAQmx to generate the same data multiple times.
00769 #define DAQmx_Write_CurrWritePos                                         0x1458 // Indicates the position in the buffer of the next sample to generate. This value is identical for all channels in the task.
00770 #define DAQmx_Write_SpaceAvail                                           0x1460 // Indicates in samples per channel the amount of available space in the buffer.
00771 #define DAQmx_Write_TotalSampPerChanGenerated                            0x192B // Indicates the total number of samples generated by each channel in the task. This value is identical for all channels in the task.
00772 #define DAQmx_Write_RawDataWidth                                         0x217D // Indicates in bytes the required size of a raw sample to write to the task.
00773 #define DAQmx_Write_NumChans                                             0x217E // Indicates the number of channels that an NI-DAQmx Write function writes to the task. This value is the number of channels in the task.
00774 #define DAQmx_Write_WaitMode                                             0x22B1 // Specifies how an NI-DAQmx Write function waits for space to become available in the buffer.
00775 #define DAQmx_Write_SleepTime                                            0x22B2 // Specifies in seconds the amount of time to sleep after checking for available buffer space if Wait Mode is DAQmx_Val_Sleep.
00776 #define DAQmx_Write_NextWriteIsLast                                      0x296C // Specifies that the next samples written are the last samples you want to generate. Use this property when performing continuous generation to prevent underflow errors after writing the last sample. Regeneration Mode must be DAQmx_Val_DoNotAllowRegen to use this property.
00777 #define DAQmx_Write_DigitalLines_BytesPerChan                            0x217F // Indicates the number of bytes expected per channel in a sample for line-based writes. If a channel has fewer lines than this number, NI-DAQmx ignores the extra bytes.

04858 /******************************************************************************
04859  *** NI-DAQmx Error Codes *****************************************************
04860  ******************************************************************************/
04861 
04862 #define DAQmxSuccess                                  (0)
04863 
04864 #define DAQmxFailed(error)                            ((error)<0)
04865 
04866 // Error and Warning Codes
04867 #define DAQmxErrorCOCannotKeepUpInHWTimedSinglePoint                                    (-209805)
04868 #define DAQmxErrorWaitForNextSampClkDetected3OrMoreSampClks                             (-209803)
04869 #define DAQmxErrorWaitForNextSampClkDetectedMissedSampClk                               (-209802)
04870 #define DAQmxErrorWriteNotCompleteBeforeSampClk                                         (-209801)
04871 #define DAQmxErrorReadNotCompleteBeforeSampClk                                          (-209800)
04872 #define DAQmxErrorSCXI1600ImportNotSupported                                            (-201174)
04873 #define DAQmxErrorPowerSupplyConfigurationFailed                                        (-201173)
04874 #define DAQmxErrorIEPEWithDCNotAllowed                                                  (-201172)
04875 #define DAQmxErrorMinTempForThermocoupleTypeOutsideAccuracyForPolyScaling               (-201171)
04876 #define DAQmxErrorDevImportFailedNoDeviceToOverwriteAndSimulationNotSupported           (-201170)
04877 #define DAQmxErrorDevImportFailedDeviceNotSupportedOnDestination                        (-201169)
04878 #define DAQmxErrorFirmwareIsTooOld                                                      (-201168)
04879 #define DAQmxErrorFirmwareCouldntUpdate                                                 (-201167)
04880 #define DAQmxErrorFirmwareIsCorrupt                                                     (-201166)
